channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: JoyGen: Audio-Driven 3D Depth-Aware Talking-Face Video Editing
item.description: Significant progress has been made in talking-face video generation research; however, precise lip-audio synchronization and high visual quality remain challenging in editing lip shapes based on input audio.

item.title: VITA-1.5: Towards GPT-4o Level Real-Time Vision and Speech Interaction
item.description: Recent Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs) have typically focused on integrating visual and textual modalities, with less emphasis placed on the role of speech in enhancing interaction.

item.title: IAM: Enhancing RGB-D Instance Segmentation with New Benchmarks
item.description: Image segmentation is a vital task for providing human assistance and enhancing autonomy in our daily lives.

item.title: SDPO: Segment-Level Direct Preference Optimization for Social Agents
item.description: To address these limitations, we propose Segment-Level Direct Preference Optimization (SDPO), which focuses on specific key segments within interactions to optimize multi-turn agent behavior while minimizing training noise.

item.title: Unifying Specialized Visual Encoders for Video Language Models
item.description: Our method, MERV, Multi-Encoder Representation of Videos, instead leverages multiple frozen visual encoders to create a unified representation of a video, providing the VideoLLM with a comprehensive set of specialized visual knowledge.

item.title: HybridTrack: A Hybrid Approach for Robust Multi-Object Tracking
item.description: The evolution of Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS) has increased the need for robust and generalizable algorithms for multi-object tracking.

item.title: KaLM-Embedding: Superior Training Data Brings A Stronger Embedding Model
item.description: As retrieval-augmented generation prevails in large language models, embedding models are becoming increasingly crucial.

item.title: Bootstrapped Reward Shaping
item.description: In reinforcement learning, especially in sparse-reward domains, many environment steps are required to observe reward information.

item.title: Hadamard Attention Recurrent Transformer: A Strong Baseline for Stereo Matching Transformer
item.description: However, constrained by the low-rank bottleneck and quadratic complexity of attention mechanisms, stereo transformers still fail to demonstrate sufficient nonlinear expressiveness within a reasonable inference time.

item.title: MuQ: Self-Supervised Music Representation Learning with Mel Residual Vector Quantization
item.description: In this paper, we propose a self-supervised music representation learning model for music understanding.

item.title: SVFR: A Unified Framework for Generalized Video Face Restoration
item.description: In this paper, we propose a novel approach for the Generalized Video Face Restoration (GVFR) task, which integrates video BFR, inpainting, and colorization tasks that we empirically show to benefit each other.

item.title: Long-range Brain Graph Transformer
item.description: Furthermore, by employing the transformer framework, ALERT adaptively integrates both short- and long-range dependencies between brain ROIs, enabling an integrated understanding of multi-level communication across the entire brain.

item.title: BatStyler: Advancing Multi-category Style Generation for Source-free Domain Generalization
item.description: The Coarse Semantic Generation module extracts coarse-grained semantics to prevent the compression of space for style diversity learning in multi-category configuration, while the Uniform Style Generation module provides a template of styles that are uniformly distributed in space and implements parallel training.

item.title: Asymmetric Reinforcing against Multi-modal Representation Bias
item.description: The strength of multimodal learning lies in its ability to integrate information from various sources, providing rich and comprehensive insights.

item.title: Aligning Large Language Models for Faithful Integrity Against Opposing Argument
item.description: In this work, we propose a novel framework, named Alignment for Faithful Integrity with Confidence Estimation (AFICE), which aims to align the LLM responses with faithful integrity.

item.title: Reconstruction vs. Generation: Taming Optimization Dilemma in Latent Diffusion Models
item.description: The integrated system achieves state-of-the-art (SOTA) performance on ImageNet 256x256 generation with an FID score of 1. 35 while demonstrating remarkable training efficiency by reaching an FID score of 2. 11 in just 64 epochs--representing an over 21 times convergence speedup compared to the original DiT.

item.title: Modeling Multi-Task Model Merging as Adaptive Projective Gradient Descent
item.description: Based on our findings, we frame model merging as a constrained optimization problem ($\textit{i. e.}$, minimizing the gap between the merged model and individual models, subject to the constraint of retaining shared knowledge) and solve it via adaptive projective gradient descent.

item.title: A Unified Hyperparameter Optimization Pipeline for Transformer-Based Time Series Forecasting Models
item.description: Transformer-based models for time series forecasting (TSF) have attracted significant attention in recent years due to their effectiveness and versatility.

item.title: Conditional Consistency Guided Image Translation and Enhancement
item.description: Consistency models have emerged as a promising alternative to diffusion models, offering high-quality generative capabilities through single-step sample generation.

item.title: SeFAR: Semi-supervised Fine-grained Action Recognition with Temporal Perturbation and Learning Stabilization
item.description: Experiments show that SeFAR achieves state-of-the-art performance on two FAR datasets, FineGym and FineDiving, across various data scopes.

item.title: Towards Interactive Deepfake Analysis
item.description: Existing deepfake analysis methods are primarily based on discriminative models, which significantly limit their application scenarios.

item.title: FlashInfer: Efficient and Customizable Attention Engine for LLM Inference Serving
item.description: We present FlashInfer: a customizable and efficient attention engine for LLM serving.

item.title: Detail Matters: Mamba-Inspired Joint Unfolding Network for Snapshot Spectral Compressive Imaging
item.description: To address this issue, we propose a Mamba-inspired Joint Unfolding Network (MiJUN), which integrates physics-embedded DUNs with learning-based HSI imaging.

item.title: ScarNet: A Novel Foundation Model for Automated Myocardial Scar Quantification from LGE in Cardiac MRI
item.description: In Monte Carlo simulations with noise perturbations, ScarNet achieved significantly higher scar Dice (0. 892 \pm 0. 053, CoV = 5. 9%) than MedSAM (0. 048 \pm 0. 112, CoV = 233. 3%) and nnU-Net (0. 615 \pm 0. 537, CoV = 28. 7%).

item.title: Bayesian Active Learning By Distribution Disagreement
item.description: In this work we propose BALSA, an adaptation of the BALD algorithm, tailored for regression with normalizing flows.

item.title: Automated Self-Refinement and Self-Correction for LLM-based Product Attribute Value Extraction
item.description: This paper investigates applying two self-refinement techniques, error-based prompt rewriting and self-correction, to the product attribute value extraction task.

item.title: EliGen: Entity-Level Controlled Image Generation with Regional Attention
item.description: Recent advancements in diffusion models have significantly advanced text-to-image generation, yet global text prompts alone remain insufficient for achieving fine-grained control over individual entities within an image.

item.title: ProjectedEx: Enhancing Generation in Explainable AI for Prostate Cancer
item.description: Additionally, we conduct comprehensive experiments on both the generator and classifier, demonstrating the clinical relevance and effectiveness of ProjectedEx in enhancing interpretability and supporting the adoption of AI in medical settings.

item.title: FED: Fast and Efficient Dataset Deduplication Framework with GPU Acceleration
item.description: Dataset deduplication plays a crucial role in enhancing data quality, ultimately improving training performance and efficiency of LLMs.

item.title: Retrieval-Augmented Dynamic Prompt Tuning for Incomplete Multimodal Learning
item.description: Multimodal learning with incomplete modality is practical and challenging.

item.title: Data Augmentation Techniques for Chinese Disease Name Normalization
item.description: Disease name normalization is an important task in the medical domain.

item.title: A Multi-task Supervised Compression Model for Split Computing
item.description: Split computing ($\neq$ split learning) is a promising approach to deep learning models for resource-constrained edge computing systems, where weak sensor (mobile) devices are wirelessly connected to stronger edge servers through channels with limited communication capacity.

item.title: CySecBench: Generative AI-based CyberSecurity-focused Prompt Dataset for Benchmarking Large Language Models
item.description: Typically, these methods are evaluated using datasets of malicious prompts designed to bypass security policies established by LLM providers.

item.title: BeliN: A Novel Corpus for Bengali Religious News Headline Generation using Contextual Feature Fusion
item.description: Automatic text summarization, particularly headline generation, remains a critical yet underexplored area for Bengali religious news.

item.title: Risk forecasting using Long Short-Term Memory Mixture Density Networks
item.description: The LSTM mechanism allowed the neural network to capture volatility clustering similarly to GARCH models.

item.title: Bridging Simplicity and Sophistication using GLinear: A Novel Architecture for Enhanced Time Series Prediction
item.description: A performance comparison with state-of-the-art linear architectures (such as NLinear, DLinear, and RLinear) and transformer-based time series predictor (Autoformer) shows that the GLinear, despite being parametrically efficient, significantly outperforms the existing architectures in most cases of multivariate TSF.

item.title: Learning 3D Garment Animation from Trajectories of A Piece of Cloth
item.description: Without the priors from analytical physics models and differentiable simulation engines, EUNet is able to directly capture the constitutive behaviors from the observed piece of cloth and uniformly describes the change of energy caused by deformations, such as stretching and bending.

item.title: Efficient Connectivity-Preserving Instance Segmentation with Supervoxel-Based Loss Function
item.description: Reconstructing the intricate local morphology of neurons and their long-range projecting axons can address many connectivity related questions in neuroscience.

item.title: RingFormer: A Neural Vocoder with Ring Attention and Convolution-Augmented Transformer
item.description: Additionally, the sequential nature of sample generation in neural vocoders poses difficulties for real-time processing, making the direct adoption of transformers impractical.

item.title: Physics-informed Gaussian Processes for Safe Envelope Expansion
item.description: Flight test analysis often requires predefined test points with arbitrarily tight tolerances, leading to extensive and resource-intensive experimental campaigns.

item.title: Are LLMs effective psychological assessors? Leveraging adaptive RAG for interpretable mental health screening through psychometric practice
item.description: In psychological practice, standardized questionnaires serve as essential tools for assessing mental constructs (e. g., attitudes, traits, and emotions) through structured questions (aka items).

item.title: Noise-Resilient Symbolic Regression with Dynamic Gating Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Symbolic regression (SR) has emerged as a pivotal technique for uncovering the intrinsic information within data and enhancing the interpretability of AI models.

item.title: Multivariate Human Activity Segmentation: Systematic Benchmark with ClaSP
item.description: In this review, we provide a systematic benchmark of dimensionality reduction, model aggregation, and change point selection applied to the ClaSP TSS algorithm for real-world, multidimensional mobile sensing data.

item.title: Diversity Optimization for Travelling Salesman Problem via Deep Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Existing neural methods for the Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP) mostly aim at finding a single optimal solution.

item.title: FGAseg: Fine-Grained Pixel-Text Alignment for Open-Vocabulary Semantic Segmentation
item.description: The core of FGAseg is a Pixel-Level Alignment module that employs a cross-modal attention mechanism and a text-pixel alignment loss to refine the coarse-grained alignment from CLIP, achieving finer-grained pixel-text semantic alignment.

item.title: LUSIFER: Language Universal Space Integration for Enhanced Multilingual Embeddings with Large Language Models
item.description: Extensive experimental results demonstrate that LUSIFER significantly enhances the multilingual performance across various embedding tasks, particularly for medium and low-resource languages, without requiring explicit multilingual training data.

item.title: RORem: Training a Robust Object Remover with Human-in-the-Loop
item.description: We first collect 60K training pairs from open-source datasets to train an initial object removal model for generating removal samples, and then utilize human feedback to select a set of high-quality object removal pairs, with which we train a discriminator to automate the following training data generation process.

item.title: Navigating Nuance: In Quest for Political Truth
item.description: This study investigates the several nuanced rationales for countering the rise of political bias.

item.title: AutoPresent: Designing Structured Visuals from Scratch
item.description: We benchmark end-to-end image generation and program generation methods with a variety of models, and find that programmatic methods produce higher-quality slides in user-interactable formats.

item.title: Cached Adaptive Token Merging: Dynamic Token Reduction and Redundant Computation Elimination in Diffusion Model
item.description: Diffusion models have emerged as a promising approach for generating high-quality, high-dimensional images.
